Boot all six machines to the multi-user login prompt. [20 pts]


Create a user with you identikey login as user name and private group name on every machine.
The shell must be /bin/bash.
Allow this user to run commands using sudo by adding the user to the wheel or sudo group.
Choose any password you like.  [20]

useradd -s /bin/bash -m oldo5582 -p "oldo5582" --user-group
usermod -aG wheel oldo5582

add to /etc/sudoers:
oldo5582 ALL=(ALL)      ALL

Ensure that all six machines can ping 8.8.8.8.  [15 pts]


Ensure that you can ssh to all machines from Machine A.
For all machines except Machine E also ensure that you can ssh from the VPN.  [15 pts]


Ensure that
dig @100.64.N.2 www.dundermifflin.com
resolves correctly. [15 pts]


Ensure that
curl --resolv www.dundermifflin.com:80:100.64.N.3 http://www.dundermifflin.com/index.html
returns the dundermifflin index page. [15 pts]


At the end of the exam, shut down all six machines.  I will power them back up for grading.